headline: 2 Reasons to Like LW and 1 to Stay Skeptical
summary: Over the past six months, Lamb Weston’s stock price fell to $53.51. Shareholders have lost 19.9% of their capital, disappointing when considering the S&P 500 was flat. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
